de.ovgu.dke.teaching.ml.tictactoe.api
Interface IBoard

All Known Implementing Classes:
Board2D, Board3D, BoundBoard
public interface IBoard

Represents a TicTacToe board. The board has a certain dimension, stores each player's move, can return the full history of all moves, is able to determine whether one of the players has won or the game is a draw, and the board can be cloned easily.

Author:
Thomas Low (thomas.low@ovgu.de)

isFinalState

boolean isFinalState()
Returns if the board is in a final state. A final state means that either one of the players has won, or all fields are occupied, resulting in a draw.

Returns:
true if the board is in a final state and can not be modified anymore
